Police have warned members of the public not to approach two convicts who have broken out of prison. The two men went on the run on Sunday evening and have not been seen since. Shawn Dibble and Carl Perry absconded from Leyhill Prison near Wotton-under-Edge, Gloucestershire. Dibble, who is serving a sentence for ‘burglaries/theft/robberies’, is described as being 5 foot 9 inches. Police say the 44-year-old is of medium build and has brown hair and blue eyes. He is known to frequent the Bristol area, according to investigators. Perry, who is serving a sentence for robberies, is described as 5 foot 9 inches. Th 37-year-old has a slim build, short brown hair at the sides and brown eyes. He also has tattoos on both arms and is missing an upper front tooth. Perry has links to the Midlands region, police said. The public is being warned to call 999 immediately if they see Dibble or Perry. Get in touch with our news team by emailing us at webnews@metro.co.uk. For more stories like this, check our news page.